Text:
I'm proud to announce that because of the American Rescue Plan I worked so hard to pass:

@USPBGC will award over $960M to the NY Teamsters Conference Pension and Retirement Fund.

That means 33,000 NY workers will have their pensions restored and receive backpay for benefits.

This is big news:

@USMC Colonel Nicole Mann led this week's launch to the International Space Station.

She's now the first Native American woman in space and the first female Marine to lead a @NASA space flight! https://t.co/wyGt0wnr2x

Too many Americans find themselves having to choose between getting life-saving medications and putting food on the table for their families.

This is unacceptable.

@SenateDems plan to cap out-of-pocket drug costs and keep premiums low will finally help change that.

As Americans pay high prices for basic medications, the largest pharmaceutical companies are feasting off record profits.

This cannot continue.

@SenateDems are working to lower the costs of prescription drugs and cap out-of-pocket expenses for the American people.

Student loan debt disproportionately burdens Black and Brown communities.

@POTUS should #CancelStudentDebt to help close the racial wealth gap, provide relief to so many, and help give an immediate boost to our economy.

https://t.co/gcXEKr6lXo

This Democratic Senate is taking aim at lowering costs for the American people. Today:

@CommerceDems are meeting to take aim at reforming unfair shipping practices that hurt consumers
@HELPCmteDems are meeting to focus on lowering the price of child care and preschool

Koch Industries shamefully continues to do business in Putin’s Russia—putting profits ahead of defending democracy

It must stop

@SenateDems, @RonWyden, &amp; I are exploring legislation to add Russia to existing laws denying foreign tax credits for taxes paid to North Korea &amp; Syria

#EqualPayDay marks the number of days a woman must work into 2022 to earn what a man earned in 2021.

Women are paid 83¢ for every $1 paid to a man. That gap is even wider for women of color.

@SenateDems are working to eliminate the wage gap and make fair pay a reality for all.

57 years ago today, more than 600 people were met with violence as they marched across the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma for the right to vote.

Today, the march for voting rights is not over.

@SenateDems will not stop working to protect voting rights for every single American.

@CUNY Rev. Dr. W Franklyn Richardson leads Grace Baptist Church in Mount Vernon, NY.

A preacher for 4 decades. A civil rights leader. He was the youngest person ever elected General Secretary of the National Baptist Convention. He chairs the @NationalAction Board.

#BlackHistoryMonth https://t.co/lFglU3bZdc

The student debt burden falls especially hard on Black borrowers:

The median Black borrower will owe 95% of their debt 20 years after starting college, while the median white borrower will only owe 6%.

@POTUS can #CancelStudentDebt now and help close the racial wealth gap.

When it’s Allen vs. Mahomes, I’m with Allen.

Bills by a billion!

@BuffaloBills #BillsMafia https://t.co/gKGCYmI6io

Americans across the country are sending a clear message:

The vast majority support legalizing marijuana.

@RonWyden, @SenBooker, &amp; I are working to pass our Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act to end the federal prohibition and repair the harm done by the War on Drugs.

@DTHballet @NonprofitNY @wearephsny @SupportiveNew @NYCETC_org @phsny I’m proud we delivered billions to #SaveOurStages to help so many theaters, venues, artists, stagehands, staff, &amp; more!

And I encourage folks to see shows—it is so important to the creativity of this city that our artists fully recover.

Watch this from #NonprofitsMakeNewYork: https://t.co/v3jBTm3VMD

Today, I was so proud to introduce Judge Ali Nathan to Senate Judiciary for her confirmation hearing.

@POTUS nominated her for the 2nd Circuit on my recommendation.

She’s now an SDNY judge, and she’d be the SECOND-EVER openly lesbian woman to serve as a federal appellate judge. https://t.co/TIY36pZmfh

Without action, student loan payments will resume in February

I'm standing with @SenWarren &amp; @RepPressley because new data from @RooseveltInst is showing this will undermine economic progress for so many families

@POTUS should extend the pause—and he should #CancelStudentDebt

The pause on student loan payments has been critical amid COVID

But an extension on the pause is needed—89% of borrowers say they're not financially secure enough to resume payments in February

@POTUS can use his legal authority to #CancelStudentDebt and help so many Americans

Americans are back to work, but 89% of borrowers say they’re not financially secure enough to resume student loan payments in Feb

Extending the pause is crucial—resuming payments will undermine families' economic progress

@POTUS can use his legal authority to #CancelStudentDebt

The message across the country is clear:
The vast majority of Americans support legalizing marijuana.
@RonWyden, @SenBooker, and I are working to pass our Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act to end the federal prohibition and repair the harm done by the War on Drugs.

Latinas earn just 57 cents for every $1 earned by white men.

And it would take them until today to catch up to what white men made at the end of last year.

@SenateDems will continue working to secure paycheck fairness for Latinas and their families. #LatinaEqualPayDay

In state after state, Americans are sending a clear message—they want an end to marijuana prohibition.

@SenBooker, @RonWyden, and I released our Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act to end the federal prohibition &amp; undo harms of the War on Drugs.

https://t.co/ND4MlKPJ5s

Republicans are the party of economic disaster

@POTUS was crystal clear this morning: If Republicans don’t get out of the way, our government will likely default for the first time ever

I will set up a cloture vote to move forward the House-passed bill to suspend the debt limit

Millions of Americans struggle under the burden of student debt, and the pandemic has exacerbated this problem

Pausing payments and interest has helped, but canceling this debt is what borrowers desperately need

@POTUS can use his existing legal authority to #CancelStudentDebt

Cities across the nation are sending a clear message—they want an end to marijuana prohibition.

@SenBooker,@RonWyden, &amp; I are working to pass our Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act to end federal prohibition &amp; undo the harms of the War on Drugs.
https://t.co/wnay3DVrXv

Devastating fires, floods, storms—it isn’t normal

@SenateDems, @LCVoters, &amp; @ClimatePower are working to attack this crisis head-on

We're working on solutions that create green jobs in communities too often left behind—like working to establish a big bold Civilian Climate Corps https://t.co/Ad9OqDNMor

Americans urgently need big, bold infrastructure legislation to build resilience and fight climate change by reducing carbon pollution.

@SenateDems' budget resolution will enable us to take this big, bold action.

https://t.co/i4ticvWrSb

With Ida—Mamaroneck's been battered repeatedly by storms

@GovKathyHochul @GillibrandNY @JamaalBowmanNY Mayor Murphy &amp; I are working to ensure OMB and Army Corps prioritize making Mamaroneck resilient

And @SenateDems' budget resolution will enable us to take bold climate action https://t.co/q8xbXwt7cc

A lengthy backlog at the IRS threatened access to the New York Excluded Worker Fund for our frontline immigrant workers.

@JessicaRamos, @CnDelarosa, @VoteJGR, New York advocates, and I just announced a new fix.

Thousands of New Yorkers in low-income households will benefit. https://t.co/ZLSvwhOBZK

Damian Williams, Breon Peace, and Carla Freedman are committed to ensuring equal justice under law.

@GillibrandNY and I were proud to recommend them to be the U.S. Attorneys for the Southern, Eastern, and Northern Districts of New York.

https://t.co/rmGdUfUbay

Today, I was proud to stand with everyone fighting to stop the North Brooklyn Pipeline.

Thank you to the tireless community groups pushing back against this harmful project.

@SaneEnergy @BvilleGreen @NewtownCreek @elpuentepalante @nychange @sunrisemvmtnyc @MaydaySpace

We can't reduce greenhouse gas emissions without dealing with carbon pollution from cars we drive

@POTUS's executive order and my Clean Cars plan are the kind of bold action we need

Dems promised bold climate action—and we're making it a vital part of infrastructure legislation

Nearly 70% support legalizing marijuana

The majority of Americans live in states where marijuana's legal in some form

@RonWyden, @SenBooker, and I released our Cannabis Administration and Opportunity Act to end the federal prohibition &amp; repair the harms done by the War on Drugs

.@RepAOC and I worked side-by-side to ensure flexibility for the families of those who died early in COVID to be able to access @FEMA's funeral funding

This is a step in the right direction—but there's still more for @FEMA to do

@RepAOC &amp; I will keep fighting for these families

Student debt is holding back entire generations of young adults from buying homes, saving for retirement, starting families, &amp; more.

This is a burden that falls especially hard on Black borrowers.

@POTUS can #CancelStudentDebt through executive action. https://t.co/oEuVVrP1DP

Student debt is holding back millions of Americans.

@POTUS can #CancelStudentDebt to help provide much-needed relief.

Proud to host a #CancelStudentDebtNY event with @RepBowman, @RepMondaire, @RepRitchie, @YoungInvincible, @IndivisibleTeam, @NYPIRG, @DebtCrisisOrg, and more. https://t.co/lIvEjpLMBs

You’re going to want to watch this:

@SenWarren is chairing a hearing on student debt, racial justice, borrowers, and the economy.

We are working side-by-side for President Biden to #CancelStudentDebt.

COVID has shone a spotlight on the inequities in our society.

@AOC &amp; I worked to deliver funding for FEMA to pay funeral and cemetery costs for NY families—far too many in communities of color—who can't afford it right now.

I won't stop working to end those inequities. https://t.co/hxn1bmE7W7

Congress joins all Americans in sadness and appreciation for the service and heroic sacrifice of Officer Billy Evans

He gave his life to protect our Capitol and we are forever in his debt

@SpeakerPelosi and I are announcing that he will lie in honor in the U.S. Capitol Rotunda

BIG—The #AmericanRescuePlan makes student loan forgiveness tax-free.

This means President Biden can #CancelStudentDebt without anyone getting stuck with a tax bill.

@SenWarren and @SenatorMenendez wrote the amendment, and I made sure it was included in the #AmericanRescuePlan.

I was the author of the original Brady background check bill when I was a member in the House

And I’m so proud the House just passed the Background Checks Bill #HR8

@SenateDems will move forward to expand background checks, save lives, and help stop the epidemic of gun violence https://t.co/2BEh5APvTn

Presidents Obama &amp; Trump used exec. authority to #CancelStudentDebt

The Biden admin has said they're reviewing options for cancelling up to $50K

@SenWarren &amp; I are confident they'll agree with Obama &amp; Trump standards and experts who say the admin has authority to deliver relief

Gun Violence Survivors Week is dedicated to lifting up the stories of people who have borne the immense cost of our dangerously lax gun laws.

@SenateDems are working for commonsense gun safety laws to break this cycle of suffering.

https://t.co/s6k9GD6nVr #GVSurvivorsWeek

In the wake of January 6:

The threats of domestic terrorism, violent white supremacists, neo-Nazis, fringe conspiracy theories like QAnon remain high

@MartinHeinrich, @SenateDems, &amp; I are intro-ing a resolution to denounce them and start an immediate FBI and intel threat review

Congress is united in grief, gratitude, and solemn appreciation for the service and sacrifice of Officer Brian Sicknick.

His heroism helped save lives and defend the temple of our democracy.

@SpeakerPelosi and I are announcing that he will lie in honor in the Capitol Rotunda.
